stylometry: Production costs is the incurred costs of producing a product, the fixed and variable costs. Holding costs are the costs incurred if your were to hold a product. The dilemma is are the costs for producing the product worth holding it in order to create a profit. Holding costs your not selling the product soo holding on to inventory will incur more costs. But if the price of the product at the time is less than the cost it took to produce then the decision to hold onto it is in question. Perishable goods are always in this dilemma but with perishable goods its always better to take the production cost over the holding cost becuase perishable foods have an experaiation date on it and if you hold onto it too long than you not only incur the holding cost but the production cost as well, and make no money.
